## Job

1. **Gateway provider** `packages/system-bus/src/webhooks/providers/deepgram.ts` (mirror
   `providers/mux.ts` + its test pattern): id `deepgram`, verification = constant-time compare
   of the `token` query param against env `DEEPGRAM_CALLBACK_TOKEN`; normalize to event
   `transcript.ready` with data = `{ resourceId: <query param>, requestId?, results: <body> }`.
   Register in `webhooks/server.ts`. serve.ts lease lines:
   `{ env: "DEEPGRAM_API_KEY", secret: "deepgram_api_key" }` and
   `{ env: "DEEPGRAM_CALLBACK_TOKEN", secret: "deepgram_callback_token" }` (both already exist
   in agent-secrets). Add `"deepgram"` to the generic dispatcher's provider list
   (`webhook-subscription-dispatch-generic.ts`) with event name `transcript.ready`.
2. **Request step** in joelclaw-video's rendition.ready path (after the patch step, guarded on
   the record not already having a transcript): POST
   `https://api.deepgram.com/v1/listen?model=nova-3&smart_format=true&punctuate=true&paragraphs=true&utterances=true&callback=<URL-ENCODED https://hooks.joelclaw.com/webhooks/deepgram?token=...&resourceId=...>&callback_method=post`
   with body `{ "url": "https://stream.mux.com/<playbackId>/highest.mp4" }`, header
   `Authorization: Token <DEEPGRAM_API_KEY>`. Effect Config: `DEEPGRAM_API_KEY`,
   `DEEPGRAM_CALLBACK_TOKEN`, `HOOKS_BASE_URL` (default `https://hooks.joelclaw.com`).
   Forensics: `deepgram-request.started/completed/failed` with resourceId + deepgram request_id.
3. **Transcript-ready function** in joelclaw-video (new Inngest fn
   `joelclaw-video-deepgram-transcript`, trigger `deepgram/transcript.ready`, retries 3):
   - Parse Deepgram results (channels[0].alternatives[0]): full transcript text (prefer
     paragraphs when present) + build WebVTT from utterances (small pure util with a unit test:
     cue timestamps `HH:MM:SS.mmm`, sensible line lengths).
   - PATCH wzrrd `POST`-style per its transcript API: `PATCH /api/videos/<shareSlug>/transcript`
     with inline `{ vtt, text, excerpt (first ~300 chars), language }`, bearer
     `WZRRD_VIDEO_SERVICE_TOKEN` (already in env/leases). NOTE: a concurrent worker is changing
     wzrrd to accept inline and store to R2 — code to the contract
     `{ vtt: string, text: string, excerpt?: string, language?: string }` and a
     `{ ok, video, captionsUrl }` response carrying
     `captionsUrl = https://wzrrd.sh/v/<slug>/captions.vtt`.
   - Patch Convex: add to joelclaw-api a `POST /api/videos/:resourceId/transcript` route +
     `videos.setTranscript` mutation storing `fields.transcript = { text, language, excerpt,
     source: "deepgram", updatedAt }` (follow existing route/mutation patterns exactly).
   - Add the captions to the Mux asset as a text track:
     `POST https://api.mux.com/video/v1/assets/<assetId>/tracks` with
     `{ url: <captionsUrl>, type: "text", text_type: "subtitles", language_code: <lang|en>,
     name: "English", closed_captions: false }` — tolerate 400 "already exists" style duplicate
     errors as success on retries.
   - Forensics on every step (`deepgram-transcript.*`, `mux-text-track.*`).
4. Do NOT restart workers, deploy convex, or run live tests — steering owns acceptance.

